00:15.533 --> 00:17.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

00:17.600 --> 00:21.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
rolls back some of Obama's
efforts to normalize U.S.-Cuba

00:23.166 --> 00:26.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
relations, reviving
travel restrictions to
the communist nation.

00:26.466 --> 00:31.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then, I sit down with retired
General David Petraeus to ask
about the Trump administration's

00:33.433 --> 00:37.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
military strategy, including
reports that it will send 4,000
more troops to Afghanistan.

00:38.266 --> 00:40.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

00:40.366 --> 00:42.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DAVID PETRAEUS, Former
Commander, U.S. Central
Command: We need to
recognize that we went

00:42.433 --> 00:45.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
there for a reason, and we
have stayed for a reason, to
ensure that Afghanistan is not

00:45.500 --> 00:49.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
