patients are getting
the right interventions.

30:21.466 --> 30:26.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: Well, as soon as we get
this ultrasound done, we are
going to get your lights on and

30:27.733 --> 30:29.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
your windows open, OK?

30:29.733 --> 30:34.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Every year, almost
six million patients land in
an intensive care unit, and,

30:35.533 --> 30:38.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
through often heroic
efforts, lives are saved.

30:38.833 --> 30:43.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For many of those survivors,
that period of time becomes
a bright line in their lives

30:44.733 --> 30:46.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of before and after.

30:46.833 --> 30:50.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL TURPIN, Was Admitted to
ICU: I am very aware that I am
not the same person who went

30:51.800 --> 30:54.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
into the hospital with sepsis.

30:54.166 --> 30:56.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I am just not.

30:56.333 --> 30:59.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: In what ways?

30:59.033 --> 31:01.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL TURPIN: Well,
my personality.

31:01.733 --> 31:04.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm shorter-tempered, mood
change, mild depression.

31:04.933 --> 31:09.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Paul Turpin,
an endocrinologist
who lives outside of
Nashville with his wife,

31:11.100 --> 31:14.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Mary Lou, spent a
month in an ICU.

31:14.300 --> 31:19.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That was two-and-a-half
years ago.

31:21.266 --> 31:25.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Richard Langford's first ICU
stay was a decade ago, and he
has not lived on his own since.

31:27.233 --> 31:30.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD LANGFORD, Was
Admitted to ICU: Mom is the
one who takes care of me.

31:30.133 --> 31:33.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Now, my mother is 88 years old.

31:33.733 --> 31:38.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Psychologist Jim
Jackson leads this support
group, and is part of a team

31:40.666 --> 31:45.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at Vanderbilt University Medical
Center that helped identify
a constellation of symptoms

31:46.633 --> 31:51.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
mimicking PTSD, post-traumatic
stress disorder.

31:51.000 --> 31:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They call it post-intensive
care syndrome, or PICS.

31:54.400 --> 31:58.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JIM JACKSON, Vanderbilt
University Medical
Center: They don't have
a traumatic experience

31:58.133 --> 32:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the way that a combat veteran
or a rape survivor would,
so they're not referred to

32:04.000 --> 32:05.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a mental health professional.

32:05.200 --> 32:06.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They really fall
through the cracks.

32:06.700 --> 32:09.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
With all of these gaps, there
just is a lack of awareness.

32:09.733 --> 32:11.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
How do you feel?

32:11.666 --> 32:16.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Dr. Wes Ely
has studied this phenomenon
for almost 20 years.

32:18.566 --> 32:22.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says the risk factors are
clear: powerful sedatives and
prolonged use of ventilators,

32:23.233 --> 32:25.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
which can trigger delirium.

32:25.433 --> 32:29.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Some ICU patients need
those interventions,
but not all of them do.

32:29.233 --> 32:31.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

32:31.366 --> 32:33.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WES ELY, Vanderbilt University
Medical Center: We had to tie
people down, so they wouldn't

32:33.433 --> 32:36.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pull lines and tubes out, but
we also chemically restrained
them with these deep sedatives.

32:38.566 --> 32:41.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So we got comfortable pummeling
people's brains with gargantuan
amounts of benzodiazepines,

32:42.900 --> 32:45.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
propofol, and other
types of sedation.

32:45.700 --> 32:49.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We put them in this cocoon,
but it wasn't a safe one.

32:49.700 --> 32:54.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when we started measuring
delirium, and then started
measuring physical immobility,

32:54.400 --> 32:58.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it unveiled this issue of PICS.

32:58.400 --> 32:59.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOMAN: Hi, sweetie.

32:59.633 --> 33:01.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Can you open your eyes?

33:01.700 --> 33:06.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: A substantial
number of patients leave the ICU
with newly-acquired problems,

33:08.200 --> 33:12.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ranging from dementia,
to depression, to muscle
and nerve disease.

33:12.166 --> 33:17.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dr. Ely has been following
some of them for six years,
and will soon release a study.

33:19.100 --> 33:23.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Preliminary data show one-third
of patients improve and get
back to normal cognitive and

33:23.966 --> 33:25.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
functioning levels.

33:25.933 --> 33:29.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One-third remain the same as
the day they left the hospital.

33:29.366 --> 33:31.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And one-third
decline even further.

33:31.900 --> 33:36.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN: We should talk about
whether we should move the tube
to the neck, OK, because that

33:38.400 --> 33:41.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
will allow us to
decrease the amount of
sedation that you're on.

33:41.300 --> 33:46.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: So, leaders
in acute care developed a
different ICU treatment.

33:48.800 --> 33:51.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When possible, they keep
patients out of the cocoon
by reducing the use of
drugs and ventilators,

33:52.500 --> 33:54.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and by getting patients moving.

33:54.600 --> 33:58.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WES ELY: Turning off of sedation
every day and turning off
the ventilator every day gets

33:58.333 --> 34:02.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people out of the hospital
sooner, it decreases
cost of care and it
helps improve survival.

34:02.900 --> 34:07.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Hospitals across
the country have been slow
to adopt the practices in use

34:07.433 --> 34:10.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
here at Vanderbilt.

34:10.000 --> 34:13.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's been more than four
years since the Society
of Critical Care Medicine
issued new treatment

34:15.566 --> 34:20.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
guidelines for controlling pain
and delirium in the ICU, and,
yet today, the organization

34:21.400 --> 34:23.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
describes compliance
as mediocre.

34:23.866 --> 34:27.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MAN: We're going to
get you every day up
as much as we can, OK?

34:27.066 --> 34:32.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Coaxing patients
out of bed to exercise takes
a lot more staff time than

34:32.666 --> 34:34.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
sedating them.

34:34.166 --> 34:37.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And getting doctors to change
what has long been done is hard.

34:37.733 --> 34:41.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WES ELY: A lot of it has
to do with people in long
white coats, the doctors.

34:41.433 --> 34:44.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The doctors are used
to how they do things.

34:44.166 --> 34:48.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They don't want to be told
to do it a different way,
and they're late adopters.

34:48.566 --> 34:52.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have early adopters in life,
and we have late adopters,
and the doctors think, well,

34:52.366 --> 34:53.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
this is an invisible problem.

34:53.633 --> 34:54.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I don't see it.

34:54.866 --> 34:56.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I don't see it as
an issue anyway.

34:56.933 --> 35:00.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They can't even necessarily
envision what it is that
could happen so much better.

35:02.633 --> 35:06.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Vanderbilt used
to release patients from
the ICU with no follow-up.

35:09.433 --> 35:14.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now it is one of a handful of
hospitals with post-ICU clinics.

35:15.566 --> 35:17.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's a way station
for patients at risk.

35:17.900 --> 35:22.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The goal is to be a bridge to
a medical world with little
awareness of the syndrome.

35:24.066 --> 35:26.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Dr. Carla Sevin is
one of the founders.

35:26.100 --> 35:28.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

35:28.133 --> 35:30.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CARLA SEVIN, Vanderbilt
University Medical Center: The
main purpose of the clinic is

35:30.200 --> 35:33.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to sort of bridge this
million-dollar intensive
care time to this
outpatient status, which

35:35.600 --> 35:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is not set up to take care of
the multipronged problems that
people experience after the

35:41.733 --> 35:42.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ICU.

35:42.966 --> 35:45.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
RICHARD LANGFORD: That
might be permanent.

35:45.100 --> 35:48.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: The clinic also
organizes the support group
where Richard Langford is a

35:49.433 --> 35:51.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
regular.

35:51.433 --> 35:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RICHARD LANGFORD: It helps
give me a structure for why I'm
feeling the way I do, and that

35:57.866 --> 36:00.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm not going crazy.

36:00.533 --> 36:05.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This anxiety, it is -- is not
something that will kill me.

36:07.600 --> 36:11.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's not something that
I have to worry about,
and keep worrying about
worrying about worrying.

36:12.600 --> 36:14.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL TURPIN: Thank you,
lord, for this nice day.

36:14.633 --> 36:19.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: As for Paul Turpin,
he is happily back practicing
medicine, and still managing

36:21.433 --> 36:24.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
emotional ups and downs,
including a lingering
sense of terror, which
is common among ICU

36:27.133 --> 36:28.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
patients.

36:28.366 --> 36:33.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
PAUL TURPIN: Fear of
ever being in an ICU.

36:34.333 --> 36:37.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JACKIE JUDD: What is
that fear rooted in?

36:37.800 --> 36:42.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL TURPIN: Being back in
those circumstances, being out
of control, being wrapped up in

36:42.033 --> 36:43.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that cocoon.

36:43.700 --> 36:46.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JACKIE JUDD: Is it what
you fear the most in
your life at the moment?

36:46.600 --> 36:48.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL TURPIN: Probably.

36:48.433 --> 36:51.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WES ELY: You know, you're
an inspiration to us.

36:51.866 --> 36:56.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Dr. Ely, who
travels worldwide to spread the
word about PICS, says he senses

36:58.500 --> 37:02.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
a momentum to shift ICU
care in order to reduce
the harm it can cause.

37:04.933 --> 37:08.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WES ELY: People were built to
be vertical and moving around,
not lying in a bed 24/7.

37:10.333 --> 37:14.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So we're trying to get back to
the humanness of critical care.

37:14.000 --> 37:19.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JACKIE JUDD: Even so, he
predicts it will be at least
five years before what happens

37:21.033 --> 37:25.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in this ICU becomes the norm for
patients being treated at the
most vulnerable and frightening

37:27.766 --> 37:29.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
time of their lives.

37:29.800 --> 37:34.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Jackie Judd in
Nashville, Tennessee.

37:39.166 --> 37:44.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And to the
analysis of Shields and Brooks.

37:46.400 --> 37:50.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's syndicated columnist
Mark Shields and New York
Times columnist David Brooks.

37:50.733 --> 37:55.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, gentlemen, it's been
another tumultuous week,
on top of several others.

37:57.766 --> 38:00.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have had the attorney general
of the United States testifying
before the Senate Intelligence

38:00.333 --> 38:02.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Committee.

38:02.400 --> 38:06.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then we learned, I guess
in the last 48 hours, Mark,
that the investigation by the

38:06.133 --> 38:11.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
special counsel into the
Russia meddling in the election
has been expanded to include

38:12.633 --> 38:15.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
whether or not the
president committed
obstruction of justice.

38:15.333 --> 38:18.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Is this a one-alarm
crisis, two-alarm?

38:18.566 --> 38:21.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Are we making too
big a deal of this?

38:21.233 --> 38:25.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: Well, based
on what the president
- - how the president's
reacting, Judy, I don't

38:25.266 --> 38:27.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
think we're making
too big a deal of it.

38:27.300 --> 38:32.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, the president, having
acted briefly presidential after
the tragedy of the shooting

38:33.966 --> 38:38.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Steve Scalise and the others
at the baseball field, has
reverted to form and gone back

38:41.266 --> 38:46.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to, as you reported at the
outset, now the man who told
me to fire the FBI director is

38:49.433 --> 38:54.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
after me because -- is
investigating me because
of firing of the FBI
director, which is totally

38:56.366 --> 39:00.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
contradictory to what the
president said to Lester Holt
on NBC, that the recommendation

39:02.500 --> 39:06.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Rod Rosenstein had nothing
to do with his decision to fire
James Comey as FBI director,

39:08.800 --> 39:11.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that it was based solely on
Donald Trump's desire, as he
expressed to the Russians the

39:11.666 --> 39:16.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
next day in the Oval
Office, to get the Russian
investigation behind him.

39:18.700 --> 39:21.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I just think that he is
behaving like a man who really
wants to fire Robert Mueller

39:23.766 --> 39:27.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and, you know, who didn't live
through October 20, 1973, when
President Nixon ordered Elliot

39:30.800 --> 39:35.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Richardson to fire Archibald
Cox and the independent counsel,
and he refused and resigned.

39:37.100 --> 39:39.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And William Rucklehaus,
his deputy, resigned.

39:39.500 --> 39:41.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And we had a
constitutional crisis.

39:41.366 --> 39:43.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And it led to
impeachment hearings.

39:43.200 --> 39:45.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The president is
calling it a witch-hunt, David.

39:45.266 --> 39:49.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The White House is saying
he didn't -- isn't going to
fire the special counsel.

39:49.433 --> 39:50.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But it isn't clear.

39:50.566 --> 39:52.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There have been
reports out about that.

39:52.600 --> 39:55.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, it
may be a witch-hunt, but
he's acting like a witch.

39:55.000 --> 39:56.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

39:56.966 --> 39:59.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: To me, we have
had this -- the idea that there
has been collusion between

39:59.966 --> 40:04.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Russians and the
Trump campaign has been
investigated for a long time.

40:04.933 --> 40:09.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so far, we have had no
really serious evidence that
they did collude, and everything

40:09.533 --> 40:11.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
else seems to be leaking out.

40:11.600 --> 40:14.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
So, I begin to be a
little suspicious -- and
maybe I'm wrong -- we
will see over the long

40:14.600 --> 40:17.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
term -- whether there was
any actual act of collusion.

40:17.000 --> 40:21.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There were certainly
conversations maybe
about some building and
some investment, but so

40:21.166 --> 40:23.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
far, no evidence of
an underlying crime.

40:23.533 --> 40:25.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But this, to me, is
not a criminal story.

40:25.200 --> 40:27.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It is a psychological story.

40:27.266 --> 40:31.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And it's a story about
a president who seems to
be under more pressure,
under more threat,

40:31.533 --> 40:36.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
lashing out in ways that are
painfully self-destructive,
but also extremely
disturbing to anybody around

40:37.533 --> 40:39.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
him.

40:39.633 --> 40:42.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so whether it's the North
Korean Cabinet hearing that
he held recently, where they

40:42.366 --> 40:47.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all had to praise him, or the
tweets as late as this morning,
this is not a president who

40:48.266 --> 40:50.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is projecting mental stability.

40:50.833 --> 40:55.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the idea that he will
fire somebody, whether
it's Mueller or anybody
else, seems very plausible.

40:57.000 --> 40:59.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
